\nwas symptomatic of Wall Street\u2019s in\nability to make up its mind on thi\ncourse of Fall business trends.\nFresh emphasis on the effects o\nhigher costs on rail earnings wai\ntypical of- the various depressant\nwhich sapped the market's energy n\nsome groups. F. E. Williamson, presi\ndent of New York Central Railroad\nsaid in Boston railroad buying ha,\nhppn rpstrirfpH\nTransactions approximated 1.800,\n000 shares.\nIssues in demand much of the tin*\nwere General Motors. Chrysler. Good\nyear, Montgomery Ward, Sears Roe\nbuck, Macy, Boeing, American Tele\nphone. Consolidated Edison, Anacon\nda. Ki'nnecott, Cerro de Pasco. J. C\nPenney, American Can. Westinghouse\nGeneral Electric, Phillips Petroleum\nTexas Corp., New York Central. Cre%\nNorthern preferred. Union Pacific\nChesapeake Ohio, Union Carbide\nLoews and Johns-Manville.\nA few specialties with sharp gains ot\nfair activity were Allied Chemical\nPhilip Morris and Coca-Cola.\nStocks which were backward in\ncluded Inland Steel, Woolworth. In\nternational Harvester. American Wate\nWorks, Howe Sound. Allis Chalmers\nPennsylvania, Santa Fe and Celancse\nNEW YORK COTTON\nBy the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK. October 6.\u2014Nea\nmonths liquidation carried Decembe\ncotton today to 7.99. with the entiri\nlist making further new lows for tht\nseason.\nEarly weakness of stocks, favorablt\nweather and larger crop views wert\nthe depressing factors.\nLate months, held relatively steady\nhowever, and in midafternoon Decem\nber was selling at 8 04. with the lis\n9 points net lower to 2 higher.\nFutures closed steady, unchanged to i:\nlower.\nHigh. Low. Close.\nOctober _ 8.3ft 8.30 s.Cfl\nDecrmber_ 8 In 7,07 8 nil\nJanuary _ 8 til 7 ti3 7.34\nMarch _ 8.113 7.3ft 7.38-3:\nMay __ 8.07 8.on 8.0ft\nJuly 8.13 8 04 8,08-1!\nSpot steady; middling. 8.35.\nNew Orleans Prices.\nNEW ORLEANS October 0 \u2018.F-.\u2014Cottor\nopened steady today, unchanged to 5 poir.ti\ndown under mild liauidation. hedge selling\nmore favorable weath